            <div type="a">
                <column>3</column>
                <head>Judicial Protection of Slavery in the Territories</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>Seeks to elucidate the different positions of Breckinridge and Douglas on
                    the question of slavery in the Territories. Douglas supports judicial protection
                    of slavery, while Breckinridge asserts "an independent power in Congress to move
                    for the protection of slavery in the Territories." The Vindicator argues that
                    the latter position is very dangerous since Congress is dominated by
                    Republicans.</summary>
                <note/>
                <look/>
            </div>
